# Scotland Crime Data Analytics (2022–2023)

This project provides a comprehensive visualization of crime and offense data across Scotland for the years 2022–2023 using Power BI.

---

## Key Features

### Three-Page Interactive Dashboard

- Built with Power BI for intuitive navigation and dynamic analysis  
- Unified slicer enables seamless filtering across all pages  

---

## Page 1 – Overview

- Interactive map of Scotland with regional-level data points  
- High-level summaries of major crime and offense categories  
- Quick comparison across various offense types  

---

## Page 2 – Crime Data Exploration

- Visual breakdown of a wide range of crimes, from violent and sexual offenses to property-related incidents  
- Includes bar charts, line graphs, and pie charts for deeper analytical insight  
- Designed to provide a detailed, big-picture view of criminal activity  

---

## Page 3 – Offense Data Exploration

- Focuses on public order, regulatory, and societal offenses  
- Rich visualization using bar charts and pie charts to explore data thoroughly  
- Highlights frequency, trends, and patterns at a categorical level  

---

## Data Filtering

- The dashboard features a custom-styled slicer that functions as a search bar, complete with a magnifying glass icon for clarity and ease of use  
- This refined filter allows users to search and narrow down regions efficiently, enhancing the overall user experience  
- The selected region updates all visuals across all pages, maintaining consistency throughout the report  
- An interactive map is also integrated into the dashboard, allowing users to click on specific regions and explore localized crime data in real time  
- The interactive map also updates dynamically based on user selections, allowing for geographic-level drilldowns  
- Note: The watermark at the bottom of the page is clickable and links directly to the original project repository  

---

## Tools Used

- Power BI  
- Microsoft Excel (for preprocessing)  

---

## Dataset Source

- Kaggle: https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/keezywallace/scottish-crimeoffences-in-2223  

